NPM-HELP(1)                                                                                                                                                                                    NPM-HELP(1)

NAME
       npm-help - Get help on npm

   Synopsis
         npm help <term> [<terms..>]

         alias: hlep

       Note: This command is unaware of workspaces.

   Description
       If supplied a topic, then show the appropriate documentation page.

       If the topic does not exist, or if multiple terms are provided, then npm will run the help-search command to find a match.  Note that, if help-search finds a single subject, then it will run help
       on that topic, so unique matches are equivalent to specifying a topic name.

   Configuration
   viewer
       • Default: "man" on Posix, "browser" on Windows

       • Type: String

       The program to use to view help content.

       Set to "browser" to view html help content in the default web browser.

   See Also
       • npm help npm

       • npm help folders

       • npm help config

       • npm help npmrc

       • npm help package.json

       • npm help help-search

